<title>Daily Commentary - February 7, 1997</title>

<body>

<center><h1>Daily Commentary<br>
February 7, 1997</h1></center>

<p><hr width=75% size=3><p>

I'm Gary Bauer for Washington Watch.

<p>

Well, there's more disturbing news out from the IRS.  Years ago
we were told that a new computer system would make the processing
of our tax returns more efficient.  Now $4 <I>billion</I> later
we're told the computer has crashed.

<p>

On top of that, the IRS is thinking of contracting out the processing
of individual tax returns.  That would mean that the private financial
information of ordinary people like you would be in the hands
of whatever company the government hired to do the work. 

<p>

They're also talking about starting over again with a new plan
to develop another computer to process returns.  Won't they ever
learn?  I've got a better idea: how about scrapping the tax system
all together and replacing it with one that's simple and fair.

<p>

The IRS is a big mess, and it's only getting worse as horror
stories of corruption, incompetence and inefficiency keep coming
to light.  It's no wonder tax season is one of the most stressful
times of the year.

<p>

American families and businesses deserve better.  It's time to
take our tax laws back to the drawing board.  It's time to let
America's families keep more of what they earn.

<p>

For Family Research Council, this is Gary Bauer with today's
Washington Watch.  For more information about us, call 1-800-225-4008.
That number again:  1-800-225-4008.

<p>

<center><b>
[<a href="/townhall/FRC/radio/wwold.html.cgi#current">Last Month's Commentaries</a>] 
[<a href="/townhall/FRC/radio/wwdaily.html.cgi#current">This Month's Commentaries</a>]
</b></center>

<p>

<HR SIZE = 3>

<p>

