<HTML><HEAD>  <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Adobe PageMill 2.0 Mac">  <META NAME="Breakfast series" CONTENT="Adobe PageMill 2.0 Mac">  <TITLE>Once &amp; Future Company Breakfast Series</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff"><BLOCKQUOTE>  <P><FONT COLOR="#000000" SIZE=-1>From <I>Discovery Institute Journal</I>,  Winter 1996-97</FONT></P>  <P>&nbsp;</P>  <H2><CENTER>&nbsp;</CENTER></H2>  <H2><CENTER><FONT COLOR="#000000" SIZE=+3>The Once and Future Company Breakfast  Series</FONT></CENTER></H2>  <P><CENTER><I><FONT COLOR="#000000">The Once and Future Company is a thought-provoking  series of breakfasts on ethics, economics and corporate employment in the  21st century, co-sponsored by Shuv Institute, Discovery Institute and </FONT></I><A  HREF="www.spu.edu">Seattle Pacific University.</A></CENTER></P>  <P><CENTER><HR WIDTH="67%" SIZE="3"></CENTER></P>  <P>We are all endowed with an ethical standard of behavior as a part of  our human culture. It is the inner voice that not only represses unacceptable  ideas, impulses and behaviors but prevents them from reaching our conscious  mind. In today's society however, other voices diminish and erode this  intrinsic ethical and moral standard, making it difficult to know and do  what is right.</P>  <P>Attendance at these breakfast meetings will show us how moral values  can be incorporated into our daily business decision-making process.</P>  <P><CENTER><B><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">Jan. 24,</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000"><BR>  Dr. Tom Sine, </FONT><I><FONT COLOR="#000000" SIZE=-1>International lecuturer,  author &amp; Christian futurist<BR>  </FONT></I><FONT COLOR="#000000" SIZE=+1>20th Century Values in the 21st  Century<BR>  </FONT></B></CENTER></P>  <P><CENTER><B><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">Feb. 14,</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000"><BR>  Dr. Richard Higginson, </FONT><I><FONT COLOR="#000000" SIZE=-1>author,  professor of ethics Cambridge University, England<BR>  </FONT></I><FONT COLOR="#000000" SIZE=+1>Capitalism &amp; Christianity:  Can they coexist?<BR>  </FONT></B></CENTER></P>  <P><CENTER><B><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">April 11,</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000"><BR>  David Murray, </FONT><I><FONT COLOR="#000000" SIZE=-1>author, lecturer,  President, Main Consulting Services, England<BR>  </FONT></I><FONT COLOR="#000000" SIZE=+1>The Character Issue in Business  &amp; Politics: Taking the high road to the bottom line<BR>  </FONT></B></CENTER></P>  <P><CENTER><B><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">May 1,</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000"><BR>  Dr. Richard Chewning, </FONT><I><FONT COLOR="#000000" SIZE=-1>professor  of ethics, School of Business, Baylor University<BR>  </FONT></I><FONT COLOR="#000000" SIZE=+1>Navigating Through the Process  of Change</FONT></B></CENTER></P>  <P><B><FONT COLOR="#000000"><BR>  </FONT></B><FONT COLOR="#000000">All breakfasts are from 7:30am to 9:30am  at the Washington Athletic Club. For more information, or to register for  the breakfast series, call the Division of Continuing Studies at SPU (206)  281-2050.</FONT></P></BLOCKQUOTE><H4><CENTER><I><HR WIDTH="67%" SIZE="4"></I></CENTER></H4><H4><CENTER><A HREF="aboutdis.html"><I><FONT SIZE=-1><IMG SRC="aboutdis.gif"WIDTH="99" HEIGHT="44" NATURALSIZEFLAG="2" ALIGN="MIDDLE"></FONT></I></A><I><FONT SIZE=-1><A HREF="current.html"><IMG SRC="image45.gif" WIDTH="99" HEIGHT="44" ALIGN="MIDDLE" NATURALSIZEFLAG="2"></A><A HREF="front.html"><IMG SRC="image46.gif" WIDTH="99" HEIGHT="44" ALIGN="MIDDLE" NATURALSIZEFLAG="2"></A></FONT></I><BR><I><FONT SIZE=-1><A HREF="ggindex.html"><IMG SRC="image47.gif" WIDTH="99"HEIGHT="44" ALIGN="MIDDLE" NATURALSIZEFLAG="2"></A><A HREF="crsc1.html"><IMG SRC="crscbttn.gif" WIDTH="99" HEIGHT="44" NATURALSIZEFLAG="2" ALIGN="MIDDLE"></A><AHREF="whatsnew.html"><IMG SRC="image49.gif" WIDTH="99" HEIGHT="44" ALIGN="MIDDLE" NATURALSIZEFLAG="2"></A></FONT></I></CENTER></H4><H4><CENTER><A HREF="index.html"><I><FONT SIZE=-1><IMG SRC="image51.gif"WIDTH="140" HEIGHT="62" NAT