<h2>April's Contents</h2>

<b>4/30/96</b>
<ul>
<li><a href="/heritage/library/categories/budgettax/bg1078.html">Is There A "Clinton Crunch"?</a>: How the 1993 Budget Plan Affected the Economy...new from The Heritage Foundation.
<li>Are you familiar with the <a href="/pff/i-new.html">Summer Scholars Program</a> from the Progress & Freedom Foundation?
<li>A bill to promote adoption is introduced and a hearing is called on the Partial-Birth Abortion Ban in this week's <a href="/townhall/FRC/hotline/hotline.html">legislative hotline</a> from the Family Research Council.
<li>New columns from <a href="/wash_times/">The Washington Times National Weekly</a> target the Partial-Birth Abortion Ban Act veto:<ul>
<li>Pruden on Politics: The stern rebuke of a <a href="http://www.washtimes-weekly.com/wash_times/pruden.5_5.html">Sunday-school boy</a>.
<li>Suzanne Fields: Time for another <a href="http://www.washtimes-weekly.com/wash_times/fields.5_5.html">killer euphemism</a>?
</ul>
<li>Individuals who save get <a href="/savers/library/15.html">third-class treatment</a> under the ordinary income tax, according the Savers & Investors League.  Their newest <a href="/savers/library/advis53.html">Congressional advisory</a> says: It's time to terminate tax bias against savings.
</ul>



<b>4/29/96</b>
<ul>
<li>The May 6th issue of <i>National Review</i> headlines: <a href="/nationalreview/06may96/feature.html">Reagan's Spoiled Children</a>; malaise and infighting are threatening the future of the conservative movement.
<li>Have you seen Capital Research Center's newest newsletter? <i>Foundation Watch</i> monitors the activities of private foundations and analyzes their impact on <a href="/crc/fw/">American society</a>.
<li>"Americans are tired of our oppressive tax code and they want a new
               system. But to get there, they need an honest and open debate. They're
               not getting it from the politicians and the media." 
 says F.R. Duplantier in todays <a href="/townhall/columnists/dupl0429.html">Behind the Headlines</a>
<li>Did the Republicans derail their own Revolution? Paul Weyrich ponders this question in today's <a href="/townhall/columnists/weyrich/042996.html">Dateline Washington</a>
</ul>
<b>4/26/96</b>
<ul>
<LI>It's almost too bizarre to be believed, but reports of fetal cannibalism in
communist China have been confirmed. F.R. Duplantier goes <a href="/townhall/columnists/dupl0426.html">Behind the Headlines</a>
<li><a href="/townhall/columnists/weyrich/042596.html">Dateline Washington</a> explores the conflicts of the Whitewater Independent Council.
<li>When character goes AWOL,
everyone is endangered. Find out
more in Family Research Center's latest radio
<a href="/townhall/FRC/radio/c96d26.html">commentary</a>. 
<li><a href="/townhall/FRC/fampol/fp96ded.html">With Liberty and Justice for All:
                                   Redefining the Educational
                                   Choice Debate</a> from the Family Research Council in now available.
<li>The Big Media, Are They Objective? Todays <a href="/townhall/infotain/humor/ccc/042696.html">Cartoon</a> doesn't think so.
<li><a href="/townhall/columnists/chav0424.html">Minimum Wage: Bad Idea GOP Fears to Fight</a> by columnist Linda Chavez
<li><a href="/townhall/columnists/rock0426.html">Hillary's Revenge</a> by columnist Llewellyn Rockwell.  Find out why Hillary is finally getting HER health care reform.

</ul>
<b>4/25/96</b>
<ul>
<li><a href="/townhall/columnists/fume0425.html">The Strangling Vines of Regulation</a> by Micheal Fumento
<li>Thousands of children will die in communist China's state-run orphanages this
year, and it won't be any accident." say F.R. Duplantier is his daily commentary <a href="/townhall/columnists/dupl0425.html">Behind the Headlines</a> 

<li><a href="/townhall/columnists/rock0424.html">Buchanan's Old Right Opposed Tarrifs</a> by Town Hall's new columnist Llewellyn Rockwell
<li>Today's <a href="/townhall/infotain/humor/ccc/042596.html">Cartoon</a> suggests Clinton makes Nixon look like an angel
<li>Have the Republicans Lost Their Vigor? Paul Weyrich says why in <a href="/townhall/columnists/weyrich/042496.html">Dateline Washington:</a>
<li><a href="/wash_times/campaign.4_28.html">Clinton Seeks to Please Gays</a> in the Washington Times Campaign '96 update.
</ul>
<p>
<b>4/24/96</b>
<ul>
<li>Should China's monstrous abuse of human rights affect our relationship with that country? <a href="/townhall/columnists/dupl0424.html">Rep. Smith on China</a> by F.R. Duplantier.
<li>Llewellyn Rockwell suggests: <a href="/townhall/columnists/rock0422.html">China: Trade Yes, Aid No</a>.
<li>Health care reform is on the front burner again. And everyone is talking about Medical Savings Accounts. Phyllis Schlafly says: <a href="/townhall/columnists/schl0418.html">MSAs are the Republicans' Best Issue</a>.
<li>According to several surveys, Americans disapprove of what they see on TV. But television executives insist that sex sells. <a href="/townhall/columnists/chav0417.html">Hollywood Misses American Reality</a>, counters Linda Chavez.
<li><i>Laughter is the best medicine</i>: Gary Bauer of the Family Research Council gives tribute to <a href="/townhall/FRC/radio/c96d24.html">Erma Bombeck</a> in his daily radio commentary.
</ul>
<b>4/23/96</b>
<ul>
<li>Town Hall welcomes <b>Llewellyn H. Rockwell</b>, president of the Ludwig von Mises Institute in Auburn, Alabama.
<ul>
<li>Rockwell discusses one of the oldest federal scandals in <a href="/townhall/columnists/rock0402.html">The Farm Trick Reform</a>.
<li>What Washington institution can make or break elections, bail out entire foreign governments, bankrupt whole industries, yet operates with less oversight than the CIA? Llewellyn Rockwell suggests that we <a href="/townhall/columnists/rock0409.html">End the Fed's Free Ride</a>. 
<li>Big government's biggest enemy is racing towards Washington: <a href="/townhall/columnists/rock0416.html">The Standard Bearer Returns</a>.
</ul>
<li><a href="/pff/">The Progress & Freedom Foundation</a> is holding a policy forum tomorrow on <i>The Meaning and Implications of the <a href="/townhall/events/welcome.html.cgi">Telecommunications Act</a></i>.
<li><b>Whitewater Update</b>: President Clinton is scheduled to give videotaped testimony on April 28; and it's expected to be a marathon session. Check out the details in this week's update from <a href="http://www.washtimes-weekly.com/wash_times/ww.4_28.html">The Washington Times National Weekly</a>.
<li>Bill Kristol predicts a Dole defeat against Clinton, and more in the <a href="/nationalreview/daily/nr042296.html">Washington Daily News</a>. 
<li>The communists in China may have nothing but contempt for the democratic values of the West, but that doesn't stop them from lusting after the prosperity that only a free society can attain...<a href="/townhall/columnists/dupl0423.html">Chinese Bandits</a> by F.R. Duplantier.
  
</ul>
<b>4/22/96</b>
<ul>
<li>The Constitutional amendment for a two-thirds supermajority to raise taxes lost in the House by just 37 votes. Get the update and other <a href="/townhall/FRC/hotline/hotline.html">legislative news</a> from the Family Research Council.
<li>The Senate Faces <a href="/heritage/library/categories/govern/bgup274.html">
Term Limits</a>.

<li>China reminds us that it's not to be trusted, in F.R. Duplantier's column <a href="/townhall/columnists/dupl0422.html">Taiwan</a>.
<li>From the May-June issue of <i>Policy Review: The Journal of American Citizenship</i>,
 <a href="/heritage/p_review/may96/norqu.html">The Spirit of '96</a> by Grover Norquist, president of <a href="/atr/1.html">Americans for Tax Reform</a>.
<li>Pete du Pont points out that good ideas don't always disappear, just because they are proposed by losing candidates.  As the flat tax resurfaces, this time by the Dole campaign, du Pont credits the <a href="/townhall/columnists/dupo0410.html">Forbes Legacy</a>.
<li>Though no one, as yet, has gotten sick, iced tea is banned from restaurants across the nation. Michael Fumento suggests that the <a href="/townhall/columnists/fume0417.html">Latest Scare is a Tempest in a Teapot</a>.  

</ul>
<b>4/19/96</b>
<ul>
<li>The Democratic Leadership Council, once led by Pres. Clinton, thinks the minimum wage hike is counterproductive. This, according to <i>Labor Watch</i>, the FREE weekly fax by the <a href="/sbsc/">Small Business Survival Committee</a>. Contact <a href="mailto:rstikes@sbsc.org">rstikes@sbsc.org</a> for a copy.
<li>Is <a href="/townhall/columnists/dupl0419.html">gambling</a> just harmless fun? Not according to F.R. Duplantier, who asserts that it increases political corruption and crime.
<li>And we thought college was for <i>edu</i>cation!...in the <a href="/nationalreview/outrage/outrage.html">Outrage du Jour</a> from National Review.
</ul>
<b>4/18/96</b>
<ul>
<li>New from Phyllis Schlafly: <a href="/townhall/columnists/schl0411.html">The Dumbing Down of America's Colleges</a>. 
<li>F.R. Duplantier emphasizes respect for a higher authority in <a href="/townhall/columnists/dupl0418.html">Unchanging Truths</a>.
<li><a href="/townhall/FRC/net/st96d2.html">Same-Sex Marriages?</a> Get the Straight Talk from Family Research Council's recent TV show.
<li>Conflict of interest for Whitewater's <a href="/nationalreview/daily/nr041796.html">Starr</a> counsel? New from <i>National Review</i>.
<li>Preview the May-June issue of <i>Policy Review</i>! Read the cover story <a href="http://www.heritage.org/heritage/p_review/may96/lieber.html">Why Parents Hate TV</a>
By Senator Joseph Lieberman. 
<li>Peter Huber, senior fellow at the Manhattan Institute for Policy Research, <a href="/pff/i-new.html">testifies</a> before the Subcommittee on Government Management.
</ul>
<b>4/17/96</b>
<ul>
<li>Flying Old Glory offends a "multi-national" community in Florida, <i>National Review</i> reports in its <a href="/nationalreview/outrage/outrage.html">Outrage du Jour</a>.
<li>The Federal Government compels us to fork over fully one-third of our income, and it uses that money to infringe on the civil liberties protected by our Bill of Rights, says <a href="/townhall/columnists/dupl0417.html">F.R. Duplantier</a>.
<li><b>Warning to North Korea:</b> <a href="http://www.heritage.org/heritage/library/categories/forpol/bgup273.html">Stop Provocations and Talk Peace with South Korea</a>, from the latest Heritage Foundation Backgrounder. 
<li>The march against the "New Right" is really a march against "old responsibilities", according to the Family Research Council's <a href="/townhall/FRC/radio/c96d17.html">Gary Bauer</a>.
</ul>
<b>4/16/96</b>
<ul>
<li>The <a href="/sbsc/">Small Business Survival Committee</a> reported in <i>Labor Watch</i> how some big unions have been soaking money from the U.S. Treasury. For a free faxed copy of <i>Labor Watch</i>, send an e-mail request to <a href="mailto:rstikes@sbsc.org">rstikes@sbsc.org</a>.
<li>Have you taken ACU's <a href="/conservative/ratings/">Ratings Test</a>? Compare yourself to your representatives in Congress!
<li>Federal regulations raise the cost of goods and services we purchase by $400 billion annually...read F.R. Duplantier's column: "<a href="/townhall/columnists/dupl0416.html">Cost of Regulations</a> for more details.
<li>"Woe Canada" in <i>National Review</i>'s <a href="/nationalreview/outrage/outrage.html">Outrage du Jour</a>.
<li>New columns from <i>The Washington Times National Weekly</i>:
<ul>
<li>Wes Pruden: <a href="http://www.washtimes-weekly.com/wash_times/pruden.4_15.html">A Kick in the Pants for a 'Fool for Christ'</a>
<li>Suzanne Fields: <a href="http://www.washtimes-weekly.com/wash_times/fields.4_15.html">Dr. Kevorkian, Be Not Proud</a>
</ul>
<li>How's the Clinton Presidential Library coming? Well, Jocelyn Elders has been chosen as head librarian! Get a <a href="http://www.clark.net/silhan/lib-updt.htm">progress report</a> (and a laugh) from Paul Silhan's Paro-Dise website!

</ul>
<b>4/15/96</b>
<ul>
<li><b>APRIL 15 !!</b> That dreaded day is here. Americans for Tax Reform holds its 3rd Annual <a href="/townhall/events/welcome.html.cgi">Taxpayer Day of Outrage Rally</a> across from the White House.
<li>The April 15th edition of the <a href="/wash_times/">Washington Times</a> is  on-line
<li>Other tax-related features:
<ul>
<li>Did you know that billions of tax dollars go to programs that subsidize special interest groups lobbying the government to increase spending? F.R. Duplantier exposes this outrage in his latest column: <a href="/townhall/columnists/dupl0415.html">Tax Funded Lobbying</a>. 
<li>April 15th isn't the only significant day for taxpayers. Learn about <a href="/townhall/FRC/radio/c96d15.html">Tax Freedom Day</a> in Gary Bauer's radio commentary.
<li>Today's the day to think about changing the way Americans are taxed. Visit the newest site in Town Hall's community: <a href="/heritage/taxsite">Tax Reform NOW!</a>.
</ul>
</ul>
<b>4/12/96</b>
<ul>
<li>Michael Vlahos of The Progress & Freedom Foundation goes back to the future in "<a href="/pff/censor.html">An E-Burst to Dow's Place</a>."
<li>New on <b>Trade Protectionism</b>:
<ul>
<li>The Heritage Foundation presents: "<a href="/heritage/library/categories/trade/bg1077.html">The Myths and Realities</a> of Trade Protectionism."
<li>Pete du Pont discusses, "<a href="/townhall/columnists/dupo0404.html">The Failure of Protectionism.</a>"
</ul>
<li>Gary Bauer of the Family Research Council identifies bigotry and and religious persecution in his most recent <a href="/townhall/FRC/letters/apr96.html">monthly letter</a>.
<li>Power has been usurped from the legislative branch; free speech is being limited; and environmental regulations have circumscribed private property rights. Are we experiencing <a href="/townhall/columnists/dupl0412.html">Creeping Socialism</a>?...new from F.R. Duplantier.
<li>What word best describes: "<i>with reference to one's own desires</i>"? Give your best guess in <a href="/nationalreview/word/word.html">William F. Buckley's Word of the Day</a>.
</ul>
<b>4/11/96</b>
<ul>
<li>Missouri <a href="http://www.senate.gov/member/mo/ashc
roft/general/">Senator John Ashcroft</a> launched the first issue-specific site on
 <a href="http://www.senate.gov/~ashcroft/termlimits">term limits</a>. Debate and vote on this issue is scheduled for April 22-24 in the Senate. Show your support and sign the
<a href="mailto:termlimits@jashcroft.senate.gov">online petition</a>!
<li>Is the Constitution outdated in the complex, technological world we live in today? F.R. Duplantier argues differently in his latest article, "<a href="/townhall/columnists/dupl0411.html">Constitution Not Outmoded</a>."
<li>They're likenesses do not appear on coins or dollar bills but they were leaders nonetheless. Visit the <a href="http://www.clark.net/silhan/hallpres.htm">Hall of Forgotten Presidents</a>.
<li>The <i>Right</i> Numbers: The Heritage Foundation releases its weekly <a href="/heritage/cd_ranking/top10-13.html">
Top Ten Facts</a>.
<li>The Family Research Council reacts to Clinton's veto of the <a href="/townhall/FRC/press/041096.html">Partial-Birth Abortion Ban</a>.
<li>Michael Fumento reports, "<a href="/townhall/columnists/fume0409.html">How the Media Reward Themselves for Dishonesty</a>". 
</ul>
<b>4/10/96</b>
<ul>
<li><b>2 hrs. and 47 minutes</b> of each eight-hour workday goes to earning enough to pay your taxes, according to a report in today's <i>Wall Street Journal</i>. <a href="/heritage/taxsite/">Tax Reform</a> is more important than ever.
<li>F.R. Duplantier exposes some <a href="/townhall/columnists/dupl0410.html">Environmental Myths</a> in his latest column.
<li>Focus on foreign policy: "The Challenge of <a href="/heritage/library/categories/forpol/cb24.html">Revolutionary Iran</a>"...new from James Phillips of The Heritage Foundation.
<li>How would you like to join William F. Buckley, Tony Snow, Mona Charen, Malcolm Wallop and others in the <a href="/nationalreview/cruise/cruiset.html">1996 Post-Election Cruise</a>? 
<li>This week's columns from <i>The Washington Times National Weekly</i>:
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.washtimes-weekly.com/wash_times/pruden.4_8.html">The Unindicted Proxy in the Courtroom</a> by Wes Pruden.
<li><a href="http://www.washtimes-weekly.com/wash_times/fields.4_8.html">Bob Dole: Father Figure for President</a> by Suzanne Fields.
</ul>
</ul>
<b> 4/9/96</b>
<ul>
<li>Read <i>National Review</i>'s new <a href="/nationalreview/outrage/outrage.html">Outrage du Jour</a>.
<li>April 15th is quickly approaching! Join the <a href="/govt-waste/Grassroots/tanlist.html">Taxpayer's Action Network</a> nearest you!
<li>Speaking of taxes...what's going on with reform? Visit the <b>new</b> site for <a href="http://www.taxation.org">Tax Refom NOW! </a> 
<li>Get the inside scoop in this week's <a href="http://www.washtimes-weekly.com/wash_times/politics.4_8.html">Inside Politics</a> from <i>The Washington Times National Weekly</i>.
<li>The Heritage Foundation's April <a href="/heritage/whatsnew/apr96lec.html">Calendar of Events</a> has arrived! 
<li>The emerging <a href="/crc/ap/ap-0396.html">non-profit sectors</a> in Russia, China, and Sweden are examined by Capital Research Center.
</ul>
<b>4/8/96</b>
<ul>
<li>The April 8th edition of the <a href="/wash_times/">Washington Times Weekly</a> is in.
<LI>"The Prophylactic President" in todays <a href="/townhall/infotain/humor/ccc/">Conservative Cartoon</a>.
<LI><a href="/crc/trends/ot-0396.html">"The Children's Initiative"</a>: How the Classroom Became a Vehicle for Universal Health Coverage.
<LI>Find out how lobbyists for big government often try to wrap themselves in rhetoric about children in today's Family Research Council <a href="/townhall/FRC/radio/c96d08.html">Radio Commentary</a>
</ul>

<P>
<b>4/5/96</b>
<ul>
<li><i>National Review</i> challenges you to William F. Buckley's <a href="/nationalreview/word/word.html">Word of the Day</a>.
<li>New from The Heritage Foundation: <a href="/heritage/library/categories/forpol/lect557.html">What Are America's Vital Interests?</a> Lecture by Dr. Edwin J. Feulner, Jr. 
<li>F.R. Duplantier talks about the #1 concern of most Americans: <a href="/townhall/columnists/dupl0404.html">Education Reform</a>.
<li>Capital Research Center issues a challenge to change lives in their recent release: <a href="/crc/pcs/pcs-0396.html">Rediscovering Heroes</a>, Remembering Dreams.
<li>"Echoes of a <a href="/townhall/columnists/fume0403.html">Famine</a> from 150 Years Ago," by Michael Fumento.
<li>It's a <a href="http://www.washtimes-weekly.com/wash_times/campaign.4_1.html">dream come true</a> in <i>The Washington Times National Weekly</i>'s Campaign '96 coverage.

</ul>
<b>4/4/96</b>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.taxation.org">Tax Refom NOW!</a> is a new site created as a clearinghouse for the various tax reform plans discussed by Congress, research and
educational institutions, and on the campaign trail. Read the <b>latest proposals for tax reform</b>, including a comprehensive
flat tax bibliography; follow links to more information; discuss tax reform with Members of Congress and tax experts in
Town Hall's Forums (available soon!); and even email an expert.
<li>Help design the <a href="http://www.clark.net/silhan/library.htm">Clinton Presidential Library</a> and get a chance to win a free album!
<li><a href="http://www.cal-net.com/claremont/edit/clintons_village.htm">"Mrs. Clinton's Village"</a> by Michael Warder of The Claremont Institute.
<li>Empower America's <a href="/empower/cndschl.html">1996 Candidate School</a> for candidates and staff members is almost here!  
 
</ul>
<b>4/3/96</b>
<ul>
<li>This week's <a href="/townhall/spotlights/">Spotlight</a> focuses on the <a href="/townhall/spotlights/4-2-96/">Tax Limitation Amendment</a>.
<li>Why a <a href="/heritage/library/categories/budgettax/fyi93.html">Supermajority</a> Would Protect Taxpayers, by Dan Mitchell of The Heritage Foundation.
<li>Peter Pitsch of the Progress & Freedom Foundation testifies at hearings on the <a href="/pff/cad/ct0401b.html">Federal Communications Commission</a>.
<li>Liberals -- a figment of right-wing imagination?? in <i>National Review</i>'s <a href="/nationalreview/daily/nr040296.html">Washington Daily Update</a>.
<li>Phyllis Schlafly asks, "Why Do They Call It <a href="/townhall/columnists/schl0328.html">Free Trade</a>?
</ul>
<b>4/2/96</b>
<ul>
<li>The <i>Los Angeles Times</i> reaches a new low in <a href="/townhall/FRC/radio/c96d02.html">editorial cartooning</a>.
<li>Are you interested in broadcast journalism? public relations? or becoming a Capitol Hill staffer? Then you need to attend one of the The Leadership Institute's <a href="/lead-inst/i-school.html">Training Schools</a>!
<Li>Don't miss <i>National Review</i>'s <a href="/nationalreview/08apr96/rusty.html">Dear Rusty</a>, where the NSA intercepts a telephone call from the vice-president!
<li>Extra! Extra! <i>The Washington Times National Weekly</i> releases its <a href="/wash_times/">April 1st</a> issue! 
<li>The American Conservative Union will release its <a href="/conservative/pr040196.html">1995 Rating of Congress</a> this Thursday.
</ul>
<b>4/1/96</b>
<ul>
<li>No fooling! American individuals and businesses spend 5 billion hours a year preparing taxes. Read about it in <a href="/heritage/commentary/op-ef18.html">A Tax Code to Love?</a> by Edwin Feulner, president of The Heritage Foundation.
<li>Hillary Clinton and others speak out on the <a href="http://www.clark.net/silhan/whatsaid.htm">Paro-Dise</a> website.
<li>Get FRC's legislative update on the <a href="/townhall/FRC/hotline/hotline.html">Partial-Birth Abortion Ban</a> and Clinton's plan to veto it in Gary Bauer's <a href="/townhall/FRC/radio/c96d01.html">radio commentary</a>.
