<HEAD>
<TITLE>Town Hall Feedback</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/townhall/background.jpg">
<blockquote>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="/townhall/tfeed.gif" WIDTH=425 HEIGHT=100
 BORDER=0></CENTER><P>
</blockquote>
<table>
<tr>
<td valign="top" width="40%">
<blockquote>
<i><font size="-1">Town Hall is the first truly
interactive community
on the Internet to bring Internet users and public policy organizations together under the broad 
umbrella of "conservative" thoughts, ideas and 
actions.  Our goal is to become the mall of ideas in which people congregate
to exchange, discuss and disseminate the latest news and information.  Town Hall is 
committed to inform, educate and entertain the public through this emerging electronic medium.
<P>
The organizations that have chosen to become citizens of Town Hall do not agree on 
every issue, yet that is why Town Hall believes our community is of value.  An 
interactive, open and honest debate of the issues within the conservative community 
will help us all in the fight against those who would sacrifice the individual and freedom
 for 
political gain and big government.
</font></i><P>
</blockquote>
</td>

<td valign="top">
</ul>
If you are interested in becoming a Town Hall web developer or intern, read our <a href="/townhall/about/jobs.html">application page</a>
<p>
If you have general questions about the web site, or are interested in a link or other promotional opportunities,   please contact
<a href="mailto:jon@townhall.com">Jon Garthwaite</a> (jon@townhall.com). If you are interested in linking to Town Hall, please take
 a look at our <a href="/townhall/about/graphics.html">Information Page</a><p>

If your organization would like to be a part of Town Hall, please contact <a href="mailto:claporte@townhall.com">Cloyd Laporte</a> (claporte@townhall.com).<p>

If you are interested in advertising on Town Hall, please contact our Advertising Sales Manager, <a href="mailto:chrisb@townhall.com">Chris Bertchie</a> (chrisb@townhall.com).<p> 


<p>
<b>Contacting Town Hall:</b><p>
<ul>
Town Hall<br>
214 Massachussetts Ave., NE<br>
Washington, DC 20002<br>
(800) 441-4142<br>
(202) 547-6368<br>
Fax: (202) 544-7330<br>
email: <a href="mailto:info@townhall.com">info@townhall.com</a>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
